<subSubSection id="1CDF5F80FFB9FFE36DC2FE05FD90AAC9" pageId="29" pageNumber="1542" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="547A0C0BFFB9FFE36DC2FE05FD90AAC9" blockId="29.[178,1085,408,459]" pageId="29" pageNumber="1542">
Diagnosis: This is the only member of 
<taxonomicName id="93C57788FFB9FFE36FF4FE05FC9DAAAF" authorityName="CHEVROLAT. Part" authorityYear="1834" box="[644,776,408,429]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Platynoptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="1555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="66B1D019FFB9FFE36FF4FE05FC9DAAAF" box="[644,776,408,429]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="1542">Platynoptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in which the basal third of the sutural margin is distinctly black.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1CDF5F80FFB9FFE36DC2FE46FF65A831" pageId="29" pageNumber="1542" type="description">
<paragraph id="547A0C0BFFB9FFE36DC2FE46FF65A831" blockId="29.[178,1086,474,819]" pageId="29" pageNumber="1542">
Description: Size: Length 9.5.0 mm; width 3.5 mm. Form: As in 
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFFB9FFE36EACFE46FBAFAAF3" box="[988,1082,475,497]" captionStart="Figs 161-164" captionStartId="52.[178,218,1513,1535]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,212,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-59@52.[178,1085,212,1498]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="Figs 161-164: Habitus illustrations of (161) Pilosirus fasciatus, holotype; (162) P. versus, holotype; (163) Platynoptera carti, holotype; (164) Platynoptera flavohumeralis, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282519" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282519/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="1542">Fig. 163</figureCitation>
. Color: Cranium mostly black, vertex with small flavotestaceous streak; cranial venter flavotestaceous; clypeus flavotestaceous; pronotum bicolorous, mostly flavotestaceous, lower sides narrowly black; disc with two narrow black lines; mesoscutellum flavotestaceous; elytra bicolorous, mostly flavotestaceous, black in distal third and along basal third of sutural margin. Head: Antennal capitulum long (
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFFB9FFE36E47FDF0FC1EA980" box="[823,907,621,643]" captionStart="Figs 70-80" captionStartId="21.[178,218,1351,1373]" captionTargetBox="[178,1100,235,1309]" captionTargetId="figure-1@21.[178,1100,212,1333]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 70-80: Antennae. (70) Isoforma fritilla, female; (71) I. goryi, female; (72) Isoforma planata, female; (73) Pilosirus brunoi, male; (74) Isoforma subgilva, female; (75) Pilosirus amazonicus, female; (76) P. fasciatus, female; (77) Platynoptera carti, male; (78) P. flavohumeralis, male; (79) P. humeralis, male; (80) P. lyciformis, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5294864" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5294864/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="1542">Fig. 77</figureCitation>
), each capitular antennomere longer than combined length of funicular antennomeres; antennal carina very prominent; EW/FW 18/22. Thorax: Pronotum elongate, anterior margin not projected at middle, side margin of disc with shallow tubercle; PW/PL 57/64; elytral not strongly explanate at sides, carina faintly visible; EL/EW 240/67. Abdomen: Male pygidium not incised at distal margin; aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFFB9FFE36FC9FD62FCC1A817" box="[697,852,767,789]" captionStart="Figs 109-132" captionStartId="39.[178,217,1439,1461]" captionTargetBox="[227,1033,212,1425]" captionTargetId="figure-1@39.[197,1067,212,1430]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="Figs 109-132: Aedeagi. (109) Ambonoides retinoides phallus; (110) A. retinoides tegmen; (111) A. caraguata phallus; (112) A. caraguata tegmen; (113) Artoadenus dius phallus; (114) A. dius tegmen; (115) A. regina phallus; (116) A. regina tegmen; (117) Aspitonis alarutinis phallus; (118) A. alarutinis tegmen; (119) A. chiapas phallus; (120) A. chiapas tegmen; (121) A. undulicornis phallus; (122) A. undulicornis tegmen; (123) Isoforma biguttula phallus; (124) I. biguttula tegmen; (125) Platynoptera carti phallus; (126) P. carti tegmen; (127) P. flavohumeralis phallus; (128) P. flavohumeralis tegmen; (129) P.humeralis phallus; (130) P. humeralis tegmen;(131)P.lyciformis phallus;(132)P.lyciformis tegmen." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297822" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297822/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="1542">Figs. 125, 126</figureCitation>
); phallic apex notably small.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
